                                                                                                                                                            <div class="content-item bd-bot exercise-list-start">
                                    <h2 class="title-content">How to Put in Your Workout Split</h2>
                                    <p>Butt kickers are a valuable exercise to boost cardio and strengthen hamstrings, calves, and glutes. They can fit into various workout splits to enhance speed and endurance.</p><ul><li>Push/Pull Split — Add butt kickers to pull days as they engage the hamstrings and glutes, which are often worked on pull days. They can be used as a dynamic warm-up cardio exercise before deadlifts, pull-ups, or leg curls.</li><li>Upper/Lower Body Split — Use butt kickers on your lower-body days, alongside exercises like squats, lunges, and calf raises. This combination covers all the main lower body muscles, while also training muscular endurance and lower body stability.</li><li>Full-Body Split — Integrate butt kickers in full-body routines 2–3 times weekly. Combine them with compound exercises, like deadlifts, squats, or push-ups, to add an element of cardio to your full-body training.</li></ul><p>To increase intensity and train endurance, try either speeding up the movement or extending the duration of each set. For an added challenge to improve strength and explosiveness, you can wear a weighted vest.</p>                                                                    </div>
